1689 typedef enum MeasurementValue_enum {
1690  IMAQ_AREA = 0, // Surface area of the particle in pixels.
1691  IMAQ_AREA_CALIBRATED =
1692  1, // Surface area of the particle in calibrated units.
1693  IMAQ_NUM_HOLES = 2, // Number of holes in the particle.
1694  IMAQ_AREA_OF_HOLES = 3, // Surface area of the holes in calibrated units.
1695  IMAQ_TOTAL_AREA =
1696  4, // Total surface area (holes and particle) in calibrated units.
1697  IMAQ_IMAGE_AREA = 5, // Surface area of the entire image in calibrated units.
1698  IMAQ_PARTICLE_TO_IMAGE = 6, // Ratio, expressed as a percentage, of the
1699  // surface area of a particle in relation to the
1700  // total area of the particle.
1701  IMAQ_PARTICLE_TO_TOTAL = 7, // Ratio, expressed as a percentage, of the
1702  // surface area of a particle in relation to the
1703  // total area of the particle.
1704  IMAQ_CENTER_MASS_X = 8, // X-coordinate of the center of mass.
1705  IMAQ_CENTER_MASS_Y = 9, // Y-coordinate of the center of mass.
1706  IMAQ_LEFT_COLUMN = 10, // Left edge of the bounding rectangle.
1707  IMAQ_TOP_ROW = 11, // Top edge of the bounding rectangle.
1708  IMAQ_RIGHT_COLUMN = 12, // Right edge of the bounding rectangle.
1709  IMAQ_BOTTOM_ROW = 13, // Bottom edge of bounding rectangle.
1710  IMAQ_WIDTH = 14, // Width of bounding rectangle in calibrated units.
1711  IMAQ_HEIGHT = 15, // Height of bounding rectangle in calibrated units.
1712  IMAQ_MAX_SEGMENT_LENGTH = 16, // Length of longest horizontal line segment.
1713  IMAQ_MAX_SEGMENT_LEFT_COLUMN =
1714  17, // Leftmost x-coordinate of longest horizontal line segment.
1715  IMAQ_MAX_SEGMENT_TOP_ROW =
1716  18, // Y-coordinate of longest horizontal line segment.
1717  IMAQ_PERIMETER = 19, // Outer perimeter of the particle.
1718  IMAQ_PERIMETER_OF_HOLES = 20, // Perimeter of all holes within the particle.
1719  IMAQ_SIGMA_X = 21, // Sum of the particle pixels on the x-axis.
1720  IMAQ_SIGMA_Y = 22, // Sum of the particle pixels on the y-axis.
1721  IMAQ_SIGMA_XX = 23, // Sum of the particle pixels on the x-axis squared.
1722  IMAQ_SIGMA_YY = 24, // Sum of the particle pixels on the y-axis squared.
1723  IMAQ_SIGMA_XY = 25, // Sum of the particle pixels on the x-axis and y-axis.
1724  IMAQ_PROJ_X = 26, // Projection corrected in X.
1725  IMAQ_PROJ_Y = 27, // Projection corrected in Y.
1726  IMAQ_INERTIA_XX = 28, // Inertia matrix coefficient in XX.
1727  IMAQ_INERTIA_YY = 29, // Inertia matrix coefficient in YY.
1728  IMAQ_INERTIA_XY = 30, // Inertia matrix coefficient in XY.
1729  IMAQ_MEAN_H = 31, // Mean length of horizontal segments.
1730  IMAQ_MEAN_V = 32, // Mean length of vertical segments.
1731  IMAQ_MAX_INTERCEPT = 33, // Length of longest segment of the convex hull.
1732  IMAQ_MEAN_INTERCEPT = 34, // Mean length of the chords in an object
1733  // perpendicular to its max intercept.
1734  IMAQ_ORIENTATION = 35, // The orientation based on the inertia of the pixels
1735  // in the particle.
1736  IMAQ_EQUIV_ELLIPSE_MINOR = 36, // Total length of the axis of the ellipse
1737  // having the same area as the particle and a
1738  // major axis equal to half the max intercept.
1739  IMAQ_ELLIPSE_MAJOR = 37, // Total length of major axis having the same area
1740  // and perimeter as the particle in calibrated
1741  // units.
1742  IMAQ_ELLIPSE_MINOR = 38, // Total length of minor axis having the same area
1743  // and perimeter as the particle in calibrated
1744  // units.
1745  IMAQ_ELLIPSE_RATIO = 39, // Fraction of major axis to minor axis.
1746  IMAQ_RECT_LONG_SIDE = 40, // Length of the long side of a rectangle having
1747  // the same area and perimeter as the particle in
1748  // calibrated units.
1749  IMAQ_RECT_SHORT_SIDE = 41, // Length of the short side of a rectangle having
1750  // the same area and perimeter as the particle in
1751  // calibrated units.
1752  IMAQ_RECT_RATIO =
1753  42, // Ratio of rectangle long side to rectangle short side.
1754  IMAQ_ELONGATION = 43, // Max intercept/mean perpendicular intercept.
1755  IMAQ_COMPACTNESS = 44, // Particle area/(height x width).
1756  IMAQ_HEYWOOD = 45, // Particle perimeter/perimeter of the circle having the

1870 typedef enum MorphologyMethod_enum {
1871  IMAQ_AUTOM = 0, // The function uses a transformation that generates simpler
1872  // particles that contain fewer details.
1873  IMAQ_CLOSE = 1, // The function uses a transformation that fills tiny holes
1874  // and smooths boundaries.
1875  IMAQ_DILATE = 2, // The function uses a transformation that eliminates tiny
1876  // holes isolated in particles and expands the contour of
1877  // the particles according to the template defined by the
1878  // structuring element.
1879  IMAQ_ERODE = 3, // The function uses a transformation that eliminates pixels
1880  // isolated in the background and erodes the contour of
1881  // particles according to the template defined by the
1882  // structuring element.
1883  IMAQ_GRADIENT = 4, // The function uses a transformation that leaves only the
1884  // pixels that would be added by the dilation process or
1885  // eliminated by the erosion process.
1886  IMAQ_GRADIENTOUT = 5, // The function uses a transformation that leaves only
1887  // the pixels that would be added by the dilation
1888  // process.
1889  IMAQ_GRADIENTIN = 6, // The function uses a transformation that leaves only
1890  // the pixels that would be eliminated by the erosion
1891  // process.
1892  IMAQ_HITMISS = 7, // The function uses a transformation that extracts each
1893  // pixel located in a neighborhood exactly matching the
1894  // template defined by the structuring element.
1895  IMAQ_OPEN = 8, // The function uses a transformation that removes small
1896  // particles and smooths boundaries.
1897  IMAQ_PCLOSE = 9, // The function uses a transformation that fills tiny holes
1898  // and smooths the inner contour of particles according to
1899  // the template defined by the structuring element.
1900  IMAQ_POPEN = 10, // The function uses a transformation that removes small
1901  // particles and smooths the contour of particles according
1902  // to the template defined by the structuring element.
1903  IMAQ_THICK = 11, // The function uses a transformation that adds to an image
1904  // those pixels located in a neighborhood that matches a
1905  // template specified by the structuring element.
1906  IMAQ_THIN = 12, // The function uses a transformation that eliminates pixels
1907  // that are located in a neighborhood matching a template
1908  // specified by the structuring element.
1909  IMAQ_MORPHOLOGY_METHOD_SIZE_GUARD = 0xFFFFFFFF
1910 } MorphologyMethod;

3700 typedef enum DataMatrixCellFilterMode_enum {
3701  IMAQ_AUTO_DETECT_CELL_FILTER_MODE =
3702  -2, // The function will try all filter modes and uses the one that
3703  // decodes the Data Matrix barcode within the fewest iterations and
3704  // utilizing the least amount of error correction.
3705  IMAQ_AVERAGE_FILTER = 0, // The function sets the pixel value for the cell to
3706  // the average of the sampled pixels.
3707  IMAQ_MEDIAN_FILTER = 1, // The function sets the pixel value for the cell to
3708  // the median of the sampled pixels.
3709  IMAQ_CENTRAL_AVERAGE_FILTER = 2, // The function sets the pixel value for the
3710  // cell to the average of the pixels in the
3711  // center of the cell sample.
3712  IMAQ_HIGH_AVERAGE_FILTER =
3713  3, // The function sets the pixel value for the cell to the average value
3714  // of the half of the sampled pixels with the highest pixel values.
3715  IMAQ_LOW_AVERAGE_FILTER = 4, // The function sets the pixel value for the
3716  // cell to the average value of the half of the
3717  // sampled pixels with the lowest pixel values.
3718  IMAQ_VERY_HIGH_AVERAGE_FILTER =
3719  5, // The function sets the pixel value for the cell to the average value
3720  // of the ninth of the sampled pixels with the highest pixel values.
3721  IMAQ_VERY_LOW_AVERAGE_FILTER =
3722  6, // The function sets the pixel value for the cell to the average value
3723  // of the ninth of the sampled pixels with the lowest pixel values.
3724  IMAQ_ALL_CELL_FILTERS = 8, // The function tries each filter mode, starting
3725  // with IMAQ_AVERAGE_FILTER and ending with
3726  // IMAQ_VERY_LOW_AVERAGE_FILTER, stopping once a
3727  // filter mode decodes correctly.
3728  IMAQ_DATA_MATRIX_CELL_FILTER_MODE_SIZE_GUARD = 0xFFFFFFFF
3729 } DataMatrixCellFilterMode;
